devdoc.author: Michael Bauer

allTokensAsArrays().details: The registry does only provide the count of valid tokens, but not a list of existing tokenIDs. Since it is possible to unregister existing token entries there will be "gaps" in the tokenID range. Therefor we need to keep looking for tokens with increasing ID until we have found the expected number of tokens.
allTokensAsArrays().return: IDs, addresses, tlas, bases, names, owners as individual arrays

allTokensAsStructs().return: Array of Token structs (relies on experimental ABIEncoderV2!)
